# Styling Rules

## Tailwind CSS
- Use Tailwind CSS utility classes for all styling
- Never use inline styles or CSS modules
- Use `cn()` utility from `@shared/utils/cn` for conditional classes
- Prefer Tailwind classes over custom CSS

## Component Styling
- Use `className` prop for styling, never `style` prop
- Combine classes using `cn()` utility: `cn("base-classes", conditionalClasses)`
- Use Tailwind's responsive prefixes (`sm:`, `md:`, `lg:`, `xl:`, `2xl:`)
- Use Tailwind's state variants (`hover:`, `focus:`, `active:`, `disabled:`)

## UI Components
- Use shadcn/ui components from `@shared/ui/` directory
- Extend shadcn components when needed, don't modify originals
- Follow shadcn component patterns and conventions
- Use Radix UI primitives through shadcn components

## Design System
- Use consistent spacing (Tailwind spacing scale)
- Use consistent colors from Tailwind theme
- Use consistent typography (Tailwind typography plugin)
- Follow design system tokens for colors, spacing, typography

## Responsive Design
- Mobile-first approach: design for mobile, then enhance for larger screens
- Use Tailwind breakpoints consistently
- Test on multiple screen sizes
- Use `use-mobile` hook for mobile-specific logic

## Animations
- Use Framer Motion for complex animations
- Use Tailwind's `transition-*` utilities for simple animations
- Use `tailwindcss-animate` for common animations
- Keep animations subtle and performant

## Dark Mode
- Use `next-themes` for theme management
- Support both light and dark modes
- Use Tailwind's `dark:` variant for dark mode styles
- Test components in both themes

## Accessibility
- Ensure sufficient color contrast
- Use semantic HTML elements
- Provide proper ARIA labels when needed
- Test with keyboard navigation

## Global Styles
- Global styles should be in `app/globals.css`
- Use CSS variables for theme values
- Keep global styles minimal
- Use Tailwind directives (`@tailwind base`, `@tailwind components`, `@tailwind utilities`)
